	Great staff and location	This is a quaint hotel right down by Union Square and not far from the trolley cars and buslines. The staff has always been very helpful. Our room was kept very clean and the maintenance and cleaning people are just great. We have been there four times now and ask for a room away from the elevators and stairs because we go there to relax and enjoy ourselves. We got a king size bed this last time and it was so comfortable that I even wrote to ask what type of pillows were on the bed!The one thing about San Francisco excluding the hotel that are bothersome to us, are the panhandlers. Without exaggeration, just taking a walk a block away, we were approached a minimum of six times for money. We love the King George but have talked about maybe not staying there next time if we can find a hotel similar, away from the Union Square area. They aren't dangerous or aggressive, and we aren't afraid of them, they are just very bothersome. We do love the King George though. And Lori's restaurant right next door, has great American food, nice old fashion 50-60's diner, and the people are great there also. I would suggest staying there very highly. It's a really lovely hotel.	
