Oct 1 2009 	Definitely a 'Best Buy.'	I stayed for a week in Sept. '09 and thoroughly enjoyed my stay. In response to several recent complaints about the hotel which I have read in reviews: There were no bed bugs; the rooms, while small, are perfectly adequate; the one elevator is small, but I never had to wait more than a minute or two. Many of the reviews have mentioned the friendliness of the staff. I can not overemphasize how true this is. Arranging tours, recommending restaurants, giving directions (even which trollys to take) made for an uncomplicated visit. One feature of the hotel that perhaps has received too little note is the location: one block from Union Square and three blocks from the transportation hub at Market and Powell. The King George is well worth a stay.	
