Aug 30 2009 	My expectations were exceeded	I enjoyed my stay at the King George. I was hesitant to book because of a few reviews about bed bugs, but I found a great special on their website and there were only 2 reviews in 2 years at the time mentioning the dreaded creatures, so I took a chance. I am glad I did because it was the perfect place for my needs. No bed bugs appeared and the room was clean with well kept furnishings. It was tiny, though! I had read about these older hotel room being small, but I was still surprised. This was not a problem since it was just me. My view was of a ventilation unit, but I asked for a quiet room and that was much more important than a good view. The staff were very helpful and courteous. I also was able to check-in at 9AM despite the 3PM check-in time. The location is fantastic if you want to explore all of San Francisco; the Powell St. Muni/Bart Station is just a few blocks away. The one negative is the thin doors with a gap at the bottom; I could hear every word of conversations in the hallway outside. If they would be willing to fix this issue I would not even consider staying elsewhere when I visit again. You could also hear some outside noise (I shudder to think what those with a view of the street could hear), but its location makes it virtually impossible to block out this type of noise and I cannot fault them on this issue.Overall, I enjoyed my stay and would recommend it to others.	
