Jun 3 2009 	Very charming great value	Terrific location near Union Square, historic charmer, not a cookie-cutter corporate hotel. Rooms not huge, but have all the necessary amenities, attractive nineteenth-century themed decor and extremely comfortable beds. Front-desk and reservations staff very eager to please; when I noticed on line that the rate had dropped (to $79!!), they let me take advantage of the lower rate. This is not 5-star luxury (the bathrooms are older, you can notice peeling paint if you are looking for it), but it is a solid 3.5 stars, with terrific showers and great comfort. I would stay here again in a minute, esp. for this price. The only problems during the stay: the message light would not stop flashing on the phone even though I didn't have a message (covered it with the phone instructions), and the heat system was very strange and I needed maintenance to come turn it off. But they came within 2 minutes. Very pleasant hotel. (Oh - and very nice lobby too, plus free wifi!).	
May 4 2009 	Wonderful Experience Great Value Location .. GO STAY PLAY ENJOY	I had a few &quot;use 'em or loose 'em&quot; air miles to burn, so I choose SF to spend a few days. A Hotwire Travel Ticker email advised of an incredible offer too good to pass up. After a bit of research on the King George, I decided to give it a try. Upon my mid morning hotel arrival, I was warmly greeted by Grecia, who not only checked me in early, also complimentary UPGRADED my room as well! The room was similar to other historic hotels I've stayed, (not as spacious as newer hotels), but certainly more than comfortable, was very charming, modern and updated with every convenience necessary. Speaking to other Reviewer's who are troubled by city noise, I'd advise if you're looking for a noise free environment, stay in the country, not in ANY city hotel! Upon returning to my room, I was always warmly greeted and asked if I required any additional assistance to make my trip even more memorable... Stay here if you're looking for an incredible location, great value, a charming environment with all the modern conveniences and a gracious staff. The King George Hotel is certainly my new hotel of choice in San Francisco.	
