Apr 13 2009 	Superb value for money	I stayed here for a week when I was attending a convention at the Moscone Convention Centre, which is a few blocks away.The location of King George is great. It's about two blocks away from Union Square, but the street the hotel is on, is not as busy as the blocks around it, which is nice. There's a great restaurant next to the hotel, the Cafe Mason, which served an excellent breakfast. There's also a convinience store on the corner, a Starbucks...everything is in the surrounding area, literally a few metres away. So the location of the hotel is awesome.The room I stayed in was a twin and it was small as expected. The bathroom is clean and sterile, but small as well, so there's no space for your toiletries but there were plenty of towels every day. The beds are narrow, but much better than they look which I was happy to find out. I slept allright here.If you are in town for sightseeing and not spending much time in the room, the hotel is great, but if you gotta work and spend time in the room, definitely not so great. The work desk and chair are basic and the room isn't that comfy, but for the cheap price, I really cant complain, I couldn't believe the location and quality for the price.There was only a ceiling fan and no air conditioning in the room, but that was only a godo thing as most of us Europeans hate the usual air conditioning cold. Keeping the windows open in March kept things cool. It did get a bit noisy in the night as our window faced an alley, but nothing bad.The staff were very friendly as well and I'd say the King George is great value for money.	
Apr 1 2009 	Excellent value-driven and very friendly	I typically stay at 2-3 star hotels because of the value when I travel. My main concerns when I was booking the hotel were: is it in a prime location to access sightseeing (check), is it clean and safe (double-check), are there non-smoking rooms (check) and does it have free internet (check). I was surprised when I got to the King George because it is a great property, with friendly and helpful staff, and GREAT access to San Francisco's many sites! This is a hotel in the middle of one of the most cultural cities in America! My stay at the King George made it easy to access the shopping in Union Square, easy to catch the BART to other sites in the Bay, and easy to get taken in by San Francisco. I recommended the King George to all my friends, and I recommend the King George if you want a great value when you travel to San Francisco.	
Mar 30 2009 	Comfortable bed clean room fabulous location!	I stayed four nights (Tues -Fri) at the King George for a professional conference in March. I chose it because of its great location and the room rate I got through Expedia. Based on other feedback on TripAdvisor I was concerned about the possibility of noise from other rooms or about lingering cigarette smoke. I had no such problems. I had no problems of any kind!  The bed was one of the most comfortable I have encountered in a hotel. Everything was very clean and the staff was quite helpful. The room appeared to be recently painted and carpet, bedspread, drapes and other furnishings were in good shape. Lots of hot water and good water pressure. The room was small - so small that I almost wished the upholstered chair wasn't there (in addition to a desk chair) - but it was fine for one person. Having only one small elevator is a potential problem, but there was only 1 or two times all week that I had to wait briefly for it.  My only real complaint was that when I had a question about the wireless service, the front desk told me to call a helpline. The helpline person quickly solved my problem, but I used my room phone to call (since I had used it to call the front desk) instead of my cell and they charged me a &quot;connection fee.&quot; I should have used my cell, but I wasn't thinking about potential charges. I wish the front desk had reminded me about the connection fee when they told me to call. I had absolutely no problems with the FREE wireless connection after that - a good signal even on the 7th floor!	
