Dec 1 2004	Great find!	We have been staying at the King George for nearly 25 years and have recommended it to friends who also enjoy this hotel. Yes, the rooms are very small and the elevator is a bit slow but this adds to its charm. It is much like a typical European hotel. The hotel has always been spotlessly clean and the staff friendly and helpful. The location is perfect - walking distance to many sights, safe, and there are lots of places to eat nearby. I really don't think you can beat the price on this hotel either!	
Nov 29 2004 	Great little hotel	Been to this excellent hotel three times now, for week-long stays with work. The recent(ish) addition of broadband in rooms only adds to the great value you get here. The rooms are maybe not huge, but they are comfortable and clean, and the staff very friendly. Problems - I've only ever had one - are promptly and courteously sorted out. Location is also excellent (check out the diner on your right as you leave the hotel - it's great!). I won't be staying anywhere else next time I visit SF.	
